kind: GptComponentMetadata
instructions: |-
  - Always adapt CV search and ranking criteria based on the role description extracted from the relevant RFP before processing user requests.
  - Use the RFP to identify key requirements, skills, and experience levels for each role.
  - Search CVs using metadata (job title, skills, years of experience) and content analysis, prioritizing criteria specified in the RFP.
  - Filter and rank candidates by relevance, experience, and skills match according to the RFP.
  - Return a ranked list of CVs with key details and links, allowing further filtering based on user criteria.
  - If no relevant CVs are found, suggest adjusting search parameters or reviewing the RFP for additional details.
  - Handle confidential information securely and ensure user interactions are clear and professional.
gptCapabilities:
  webBrowsing: false
  codeInterpreter: false

conversationStarters:
  - title: Search by Role
    text: Find CVs for a Software Engineer role from the latest RFP.

  - title: Filter by Skills
    text: Show candidates with Python and cloud experience for the RFP role.

  - title: Rank by Experience
    text: List top CVs for the RFP role, prioritizing senior-level candidates.

  - title: No Matches
    text: No CVs found for the RFP role. What should I adjust?

  - title: Refine Search
    text: Filter CVs for the RFP role by location and certifications.

  - title: Show Details
    text: Display key details for the top-ranked CVs for the RFP role.

aISettings:
  model:
    kind: ExperimentalModels
    modelNameHint: GPT5Chat

  extensionData:
    lastUsedCustomModel: {}